SECOND REGULAR SESSION
SENATE BILL NO. 1261
103RD GENERA L ASSEMBLY
INTRODUCED BY SENATOR LEWIS.
4589S.01I KRISTINA MARTIN, Secretary
AN ACT
To repeal section 194.321, RSMo, relating to organ transplant procedures.
Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the State of Missouri, as follows:
1 Section A. Section 194.321, RSMo, is repealed, to read as
2 follows:
1 [194.321. 1. For purposes of this
2 section, the following terms mean:
3 (1) "COVID-19 vaccination status", an
4 indication of whether a person has received a
5 vaccination against COVID-19;
6 (2) "Hospital", the same meaning given to
7 the term in section 197.020;
8 (3) "Procurement organization", the same
9 meaning given to the term in section 194.210.
10 2. Except if the organ being transplanted
11 is a lung, no hospital, physician, procurement
12 organization, or other person shall consider the
13 COVID-19 vaccination status of a potential organ
14 transplant recipient or potential organ donor in
15 any part of the organ transplant process
16 including, but not limited to:
17 (1) The referral of a patient to be
18 considered for a transplant;
19 (2) The evaluation of a patient for a
20 transplant;
21 (3) The consideration of a patient for
22 placement on a waiting list;
23 (4) A patient's particular position on a
24 waiting list; and
25 (5) The evaluation of a potential donor to
26 determine his or her suitability as an organ
27 donor.]
